28/10/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- The head of the OSCE Presence in Tirana, Ambassador Pavel Vacek, delivered to Prime Minister Fatos Nano on Wednesday (27 October) a set of expert reviews of Albanian media legislation.
The reviews assess the extent to which the legislation complies with EU standards and recommend steps for achieving better harmonisation.
They were drafted by independent experts and commissioned by the OSCE Representative on Freedom of the Media, Miklos Haraszti, who praised the government's willingness to strengthen the legislation.
(OSCE press release, ATA - 27/10/04)
